name: Lawrence CULBERSON, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS PHILADELPHIA COUNTY, Respondent
name_abbreviation: Culberson v. Court of Common Pleas Philadelphia County

parties: Lawrence CULBERSON, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS PHILADELPHIA COUNTY, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 2nd day of December, 2015, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is GRANTED, the Petition for Writ of Mandamus and/or Extraordinary Relief is GRANTED to the extent it seeks mandamus relief, and the Court of Common Pleas of Philadelphia County is DIRECTED to dispose of Petitioner’s pending filing within 90 days.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.
